Sally has 3 brothers. Her brothers have 2 sisters. How many sisters does Sally have? Explain your answer
To determine how many sisters Sally has, we need to look at the relationship between her and her siblings. Since she has 3 brothers, it can be inferred that they all share the same parents. Therefore, their sisters would also be Sally's sisters. Her brothers have 2 sisters, which means there are a total of 3 + 2 = 5 sisters in the family. So, Sally has 5 sisters.
